.:: Puzzle 2x5-Level-4-11::.
5 different games are played: bridge, mah-jongg, scrabble, go, monopoly
City: berlin, colone, boston, miami, new-york
1. the person playing monopoly is on the left of the person traveling to miami##1
2. the person playing bridge is on the left or right of the person traveling to colone##3
3. the person playing bridge is between the person traveling to boston and the person traveling to colone##2
4. the person traveling to new-york is on the right of the person traveling to boston##1
5. the person traveling to new-york is the person playing scrabble##1
6. the person traveling to new-york is in an odd position##4
7. the person playing mah-jongg is on the far left or far right##3

.:: Answer ::.
|         |     1     |    2     |       3       |     4      |   5    |
| Game    | mah-jongg    | monopoly  | bridge      | go     | scrabble |
| City   | berlin | colone | miami | boston | new-york |

